messages.message: When I make a ground truth dataset for my app, after it runs it keeps saying its outdated but noone would have edited the app so I'm confused. As a result, it doesn't let me view the dataset
which app version did you use to create your ground truth set? are there newer app versions than that app version?
what do you need to do with the ground truth set? you should be able to run an accuracy test with an outdated ground truth set
i want to open it in human review
and no, only 1 version and no edits were made to the app

~i read the error message in the modal more closely this time~ :sweat_smile:

~did you create a project files ground truth set?~

~the message says “The schema for your project changed” - we show that the ground truth set is outdated if the project schema / files don’t match the schema / files in the project files ground truth set~
i did project files yes but i didn't edit the app at all after
@pauline.comising can you help investigate why the ground truth set is in `OUTDATED` status?
@Udit can you provide the link to your ground truth set, so that we can look up logs / db entries for this ground truth set?
Yep I can, also if the gt set name still has a hyperlink you can navigate to the ground truth set and there will be a button to open human review in the top right

And yep a project files app is outdated if the files in the project are different than the files in the ground truth set (so outside app edits). So if it looks like the files are the same, I can take a look for bugs in how the filenames are compared, which can be weird if there are duplicate filenames, etc.

Oh I can still open it up through the name and then more actions!

Here is the link though: https://crafting-aihub--udit-dev-instabase.instabase.site.sandboxes.run/hub/apps/72a22a7a-e92c-4d9a-8c59-65a06a3e0e8e/ground-truths
I assume its something to do with file name which is why it says outdated
@Udit out of curiosity why did you think you couldn't edit the ground truth data set? Want to learn a little more about the behavior so that we can make this more intuitive in the future.

In the past when I made one, it said "Review required" with an edit icon beside it I had to click that immediately opens it in HR.

I didn't realize that clicking the dataset name takes me to a page where I have the option to edit it. Also within that page, the edit option is hidden under "More options". More Options at the moment only has 1 option under it too.
ok cool we're going to be changing some of that! Thanks for providing the context (cc: @Jianqi Xing)
